G.E.A.R.
May 19 at 5:12 PM ·

Many people have been wondering what is going to happen with summer GEAR activities. Unfortunately, we don't know yet. We are holding out hope for a regular June/July season...but that is unlikely. Our best hope might be playing more games in July. Once we find out what is possible for the summer, we will post. If the season is cancelled or parents/players are not comfortable playing, we will either void checks, give cash back if paid with cash, or give credit towards next GEAR sport. We should have a better idea around June 1st.

APPAREL ORDER UPDATE:
The River Ridge Middle School Student Council would like to THANK YOU for placing an order for the 2019-2020 Spirit Wear. We had an overwhelming response to this event. The total number of items ordered 847! Thank you for making our first attempt at a school wide order a HUGE success.

We spoke with the print company on 12/11/2019 to see when they would have our order ready. They are hoping to get it to us by 12/19/2019 but cannot guarantee that the full order will be ready. This is due to the large number of items along with all of their other holiday and regular orders.

We apologize for any inconvenience that this will cause. We know that some of you are wanting to use them as holiday gifts we will do our best to get your orders to you ASAP.

To ensure that we do not run into this time crunch next year we will send the order forms out in October. We were not expecting (but are very appreciative) to have the number of orders that we did this first year.

With Many Sincere Thanks

River Ridge Middle School Student Council
Lisa Haas & Alaina Klippert

We have also had the pleasure of helping raise money for a memorial fund at River Ridge school in honor of Mr. Ed Curry. I worked with Ed on his FFA shirts and he was definitely a person that loved his students and really enjoyed his job. We had almost 400 shirts ordered for him from all over the area and even had to ship some orders to southern IL. The ordering is open again for a short time if you still need to order. Mr. Curry will definitely be missed by many.

post_text:
Did you know that over 1 billion people on this planet do

not have eye glasses that need them? The River Ridge 7th graders have partnered again to help the Warrens Lions Club visions program. All the donations will help by making the glasses or get the money to make glasses. We are collecting hearing aids, glasses, old cell phones,old keys, ink cartridges,pop tabs, bottle caps, and Christmas lights.It starts NOW until March 3rd. Why are we doing this? We are doing this because it's the right thing to do. Our goal is 3,080 glasses. Where can you drop them off? You can give them to a River Ridge 7th grader, give your supplies to the River Ridge office,or give your supplies to Kim Thorsen. You can contact Kim Thorsen at kthorsen@riverridge210.org or call her at 815-858-9005.



Your River Ridge 7th graders

--
Kim Thorsen
River Ridge Middle School
Literature

Hanover, IL 61041

Tonight’s RRSM game in East Dubuque holds a special meaning as both teams are joinining together to support a 5 year old from East Dubuque who has recently been diagnosed with a brain tumor for a second time. All fans are encouraged to wear grey to support this young man who is beginning radiation in Iowa City. There will be silent auctions and donation jars and a halftime shootout.
Our Wildcat family thanks you in advance for any support you can give this family throughout tonight’s fundraiser! As always - GO CATS!

post_text: It is true that over 1 billion people are in need of vision care in the world. Warren Lions' Club and River Ridge 7th grade are teaming up to help. Together they are accepting donations. To help these people, gather your keys, bottle caps, cell phones, ink cartridges, hearing aides, Christmas lights, pop tabs, and eyeglasses. You can help by making donations and helping spread the word. Any donations can be brought to Mrs. Thorsen's room or contact her. Email is: kthorsen@riverridge210.org. phone number is: 815-858-9005. DONATIONS NEEDED! PLEASE DO YOUR PART TO MAKE THIS WORLD A BETTER PLACE! This announcement brought to you by Tyson H.
